From 2c9fa529b58d2868633b038e9263b3140e7d76f5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 14:28:42 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] DOC E-UNION: provenance/license header for borrowed
 algorithms (comment-only)

Adds a single provenance block at the top of the #ifdef EUNION region naming the
license + URL of every project whose ALGORITHM was independently reimplemented:
gVisor overlay (Apache-2.0) for copy-up/whiteout/opaque/readdir-merge, and the
Linux overlayfs docs for semantics. States explicitly that no third-party source
is copied/translated (the E-UNION C is under this file's existing license) and
that PRoot (GPL-2) was reviewed but no PRoot code/design is used.

The per-algorithm inline citations ("Modeled on gVisor copy_up.go", etc.) already
existed; this centralizes the license + URL so provenance is unambiguous in the
shipped source, not only in the workspace DESIGN.md.

Comment-only, inside #ifdef EUNION -> OFF builds byte-identical; hermetic suite
222/222 green.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 .../src/linux_premigration/vchroot_userspace.c   | 16 ++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+)

diff --git a/darling/src/libsystem_kernel/emulation/src/linux_premigration/vchroot_userspace.c b/darling/src/libsystem_kernel/emulation/src/linux_premigration/vchroot_userspace.c
index fa504996ba1b091b6747d3a2f7a572d056792f21..aa27186b76a0e7934ac26c4f73608ef6b635281a 100644
--- a/darling/src/libsystem_kernel/emulation/src/linux_premigration/vchroot_userspace.c
+++ b/darling/src/libsystem_kernel/emulation/src/linux_premigration/vchroot_userspace.c
@@ -71,6 +71,22 @@ static char prefix_path[4096] = {0}; // MUST NOT end with '/'
 static int prefix_path_len = -1;
 
 #ifdef EUNION
+// ============================ E-UNION provenance ============================
+// The E-UNION code in this file (all #ifdef EUNION blocks: union resolve,
+// copy-up, whiteout/opaque, readdir-merge, template protection) is new C written
+// for Darling and is covered by this file's existing license. No third-party
+// source code is copied or translated in. The union/copy-up/whiteout/merge
+// ALGORITHMS are independently reimplemented from concepts in:
+//   * gVisor overlay (Apache-2.0) -- https://github.com/google/gvisor
+//       pkg/sentry/fsimpl/overlay/{copy_up,directory,overlay}.go. gVisor is Go;
+//       this is C over raw Linux syscalls with a different cross-process
+//       atomicity model, i.e. an independent reimplementation of the idea, not a
+//       derivative of gVisor's code. Cited inline below for auditability.
+//   * Linux overlayfs docs (Documentation/filesystems/overlayfs.rst) -- semantics.
+// PRoot (GPL-2, https://github.com/proot-me/proot) was reviewed but NO PRoot code
+// or design is used here; the path engine is Darling's own vchroot.
+// ===========================================================================
+//
 // E-UNION (dar-test-infra-sp5.8.4.4): shared read-only system template that
 // the writable per-prefix layer (prefix_path) is unioned over. When a guest
 // path is absent in prefix_path it falls back to libexec_path. Empty/unset
